data.name: ABOUT_lblAboutDescription_Text
data.value: Conga X-Author for Excel intelligently interacts between Microsoft Excel, Chatter, and Salesforce using embedded configurable ribbons. The technology allows all tasks performed within a Microsoft Excel Document to be shared and completely captured in any Structured Data System including Salesforce, without the need to go into Salesforce or Chatter.

data.name: DM_Help_Text
data.value:
Use the Data Migration Dashboard to create a new Data Migration App or update an existing App. The purpose of the Data Migration Wizard is to help you create a fully-formed app that you can use to easily move data from one Org to another. To build your app, take the following actions:
1. Click on Add Objects to add one or more Objects to your App. Objects are added and assigned a sequence in the order you select them. Object Name and ID fields are automatically added. 2. After you add an Object, click on the Field link to add more Fields from that Object to your data migration. 3. Choose an External Field for your Object if one or more External Field’s exist. Click Not Set in the Object row to choose the External Field. Each Object must have an External Field set for Data Migration to execute. For help with creating External Field’s, consult relevant source documentation or use the Conga External Field Utility. 4. Click on Add Lookups to add Lookup fields to one or more Objects in your App. All Objects referenced by a Lookup field must have already been added to the app. 5. Choose a User Action (Search & Select, or Query) for each Object. When the Data Migration app is executed and data is retrieved from the source org, these actions determine how that data is retrieved. You can also specify filter criteria and logic for each Object in the app. 6. Copies an Object on the Dashboard, if you want to specify a separate set of filter criteria for the same Object. Make sure to change the Object Name on the Dashboard before you save (it must be unique). 7. You can remove an Object from the App by clicking on the icon under the Remove column. 8. Click Settings to configure any additional settings as required. 9. Click Save App or Update App to save your changes. The app is created or updated. You can continue to use X-Author Designer to make further changes to the app before it is used.
Note: Certain actions are restricted when you Update an app using the Data Migration Wizard. Refer to product documentation for a comprehensive list.
For detailed step-by-step instructions for creating your Data Migration App, refer to the X-Author for Excel Designer & Runtime Guide. To reach the guide, log in to the Conga community at: https://apttusportal.force.com/community, and choose Resources , Product Docs and click on X-Author for Excel.
